Caves found near Mutnovsky volcano, in the Russian Far East, 45 miles (72km) south of Petropavlovsk-Kamchatsky .
Photographer, from Kamchatka, trekked inside the dangerous caves - which could collapse at any moment - to capture the colourful scenes .
The amazing images reveal a kaleidoscope of colours in icy caves - lit up by flares and fire-breathing .